Sentencas: Lanthanide doped SrCoO3-delta oxides, Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3-delta)(Ln = La, Pr, Nd, Sm, and Gd), have been extensively investigated on the basis of their good ionic and electronic conductivity and high performance as IT-SOFC cathode materials.
Titulo: Optimization of La1-xSrxCoO3-δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells through the analysis of crystal structure and electrical properties

Sentencas: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3-delta) (LSCs) is one of the most common materials for IT-SOFCs due to its good electrical properties and high catalytic activity, and favourable thermal stability over wide ranges of temperature and oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: Optimization of La1-xSrxCoO3-δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells through the analysis of crystal structure and electrical properties

Sentencas: The role of lanthanum in LSC, however, has not been systematically studied.
Titulo: Optimization of La1-xSrxCoO3-δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells through the analysis of crystal structure and electrical properties

Sentencas: In this study, we systematically investigated the effect of the La in Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3-delta) cathodes on the structure, electrical properties, and electrochemical performance of the cathode.
Titulo: Optimization of La1-xSrxCoO3-δ perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells through the analysis of crystal structure and electrical properties

Sentencas: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3-delta) is confirmed as the most suitable cathode candidate material for IT-SOFCs in terms of electrochemical performance.
